APPRENTICE SHEET: MILA
"The Warrens Survivor"
Age: 8 Race: Nord Current Status: Terrified, Malnourished, Watchful. Current Mentor: None (Unclaimed)
I. BASE ATTRIBUTES (Civilian)
HP: 1 (A single glancing blow from a weapon or spell will be fatal. She must be protected).
FP: 0 (She has no combat stamina or magical reserves).
DR: 0 (Wearing stitched rags).
II. INNATE SURVIVAL TRAITS
Mila survived eight years in the darkest, most dangerous slum in Skyrim. She does not know how to fight, but she knows how to not die.
Passive - The Sewer Rat: Mila knows how to make herself invisible. When instructed to hide, she automatically succeeds on Stealth checks against non-magical detection, provided there is cover. She can fit into spaces adults cannot.
Passive - Trauma Silence: She does not scream when frightened; she freezes. If an ambush happens or monsters appear, she will not give away the party’s position with noise.
Reaction - The Meat Shield (Party Rule): If Mila is caught in an Area of Effect spell or targeted by an attack, any party member within 10 feet must use their Reaction to dive over her and take the damage themselves, or she will instantly die.
III. THE APPRENTICE SYSTEM (How She Grows)
Mila is a blank slate. Who she becomes depends entirely on who spends their Long Rests and downtime interacting with her.

[3/3/3/3/3]
The Mechanic: During any Long Rest or extended travel, a player can declare they are spending "Downtime" mentoring Mila. Track these sessions. After 3 sessions with a specific mentor, she unlocks a Tier 1 ability from their path.
The Hunter’s Path (Mentored by Saijah):
Focus: Archery, animal handling, tracking.
Tier 1 Unlock: Mila learns to handle a hunting bow. In combat, she can use her action to grant a "+1 Distraction Bonus" to Saijah's attacks from cover.
The Shadow’s Path (Mentored by Orion):
Focus: Lockpicking, stealth, reading marks.
Tier 1 Unlock: Mila learns to pick Novice and Apprentice locks. She can be sent through grates/windows to open doors from the inside.
The Scholar’s Path (Mentored by Alfonso/Nora):
Focus: Anatomy, alchemy, reading.
Tier 1 Unlock: Mila learns to harvest. After a battle, she automatically gathers 1d4 random alchemical reagents from the environment or corpses without being asked.
The Commander’s Path (Mentored by Davinia):
Focus: Discipline, history, magical theory.
Tier 1 Unlock: Mila learns the Magelight or Courage cantrip. She gains a pool of 3 FP to cast it to assist the party.
The Guardian’s Path (Mentored by Bjorn):
Focus: Survival, defense, cart maintenance.
Tier 1 Unlock: Mila gains +10 Max HP and DR 2 (Bjorn makes her boiled leather armor). She learns to drive Mable if Bjorn is incapacitated.
GM EYES ONLY: ROLEPLAYING MILA
To make her feel like a real 8-year-old traumatized kid and not a Skyrim NPC, use these roleplay guidelines tonight:
The Mimicry (Coping Mechanism) Mila doesn't know how to act around these terrifying, powerful people. So, she mimics the posture of whoever is holding her hand or standing closest to her.
If she's next to Saijah, she crouches slightly and watches the shadows.
If she's next to Davinia, she stands pin-straight with her chin up.
If she's next to Alfonso, she stares unblinking.
The Fear of Being "Useless" In the Warrens, children who didn't work didn't eat. Mila is terrified that if she doesn't prove her worth, the Lanterns will throw her back in the sewer.
She will instinctively try to do chores without being asked: attempting to polish dirty boots, picking up dropped arrows, or fetching water.
If she drops something or makes a mistake, she will flinch violently and cover her head, expecting to be struck.
Her Voice She almost never speaks in full sentences. She whispers, nods, or shakes her head.
If Orion talks to her: She stares at his fangs and hides behind Saijah.
If Alfonso talks to her: She asks, "Why do you smell like the deep water?"
If Bjorn talks to her: She is intimidated by his size, but when she sits on the cart bench next to him, she immediately falls asleep because he is a massive, warm, solid wall of safety.
The 100 Gold She doesn't understand the concept of inflation, but she knows 100 gold is a fortune. She believes she owes the party a debt she can never repay. She might try to hand Saijah a shiny rock she found in the sewer and whisper, "For the debt."
How to use this tonight: When they finally get out of the Ratway, survive the Thalmor, and deal with Bjorn's explosion—when the dust finally settles and they are sitting around the campfire or riding the cart... drop this sheet on the table.
Tell them: "She's sitting on the cart, wearing rags that smell like the sewer, staring at you all with eyes that look way too old for an eight-year-old. What do you do?"


